Crear una nueva columna llamada age group

chlstrl <- chlstrl %>% 
  mutate(
    ageGroup = case_when(
      age > 10 & age <= 40 ~ "(10-40]",
      age > 40 & age <= 70 ~ "(40-70]",
      age > 70 & age <= 100 ~ "(70-100]"
    )
  )

Ejercicio 2: Funciones de R

Crea la funcin cambiosSigno

cambiosSigno = function(x){
  i = 0
  for(k in seq(length(x)-1)){
    if( x[ k ] * x[ k+1 ] < 0){
      i = i + 1
    }
  }
  return(i)
}

valores = c(-10:-1, 1:10)
(x = sample(valores, 20, replace = TRUE))
##  [1] -5 -9  4 -3  9  6 -8 -5 -8 -1 -9  3  5 -4 -7 -1  9 -6 -8  2
(cambiosSigno(x))
## [1] 9

Crea la funcin cambiosSignoPos

cambiosSignoPos = function(x) {
  pos = c()
  for(k in seq(length(x) - 1)){
    if(x[k]*x[k+1]<0){
      pos = append(pos, k+1)
    }
  }
  if(is.null(pos) == TRUE){
    print("No ha habido cambio de signo")
  } else {
    return(pos)
  }
}

valores = c(-10:-1, 1:10)
(x = sample(valores, 20, replace = TRUE))
##  [1]  10  -7   8   7  10   4 -10  -7   1  -9   1  -7   7   5  -3  -4  -6   4   9
## [20]  -5
(cambiosSignoPos(x))
##  [1]  2  3  7  9 10 11 12 13 15 18 20
